content:
Analyze Your Data

Salesforce Analytics Tools

Reports and Dashboards

Manage Your Reports and Dashboards on Analytics Home

Build a Report

* Required editions: Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
* Build a report in Lightning Experience or Salesforce Classic using Report Builder or Lightning Report Builder
* Use filters, groups, and summaries to answer business questions
* Add charts for a visual overview of data
* Refresh preview as you build

Show Report Data Graphically

* Show data in chart form to help readers understand the data quickly
* Use line charts, bar charts, or pie charts
* Charts can appear above the report table and in dashboard widgets

Show Report Data in Tables

* Hide details and ranges, limit results shown, and highlight with color
* Show tables in dashboard widgets

Categorize Data with Bucket Columns

* Quickly categorize report records without creating a formula or custom field by bucketing them
* Define multiple categories (buckets) used to group report values

Evaluate Report Data with Formulas

* Use built-in basic math functions (sum, average, min, max)
* Write formulas for advanced logical or mathematical operations

Count Unique Values in Report Results

* See how many distinct values a column returns with a unique count

Combine Different Types of Information in a Joined Report

* View different types of information in a single report
* Join reports using the report builder

Report on Historical Changes

* Analyze day-to-day and week-to-week changes in opportunities, cases, forecasts, and custom objects

Report Type Reference

* Choose a report type to determine which records and fields appear in your report
title: Building and Customizing Reports
